<SLUG> BC-OBIT-MCCARTHY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JOSEPH LEPAGE MCCARTHY, WOOD CHEMISTRY EXPERT, DIES AT 86 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Attn: Wash.)   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Joseph LePage McCarthy, an expert in wood chemistry, died on
Monday in Seattle. He was 86 and lived in Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   He was also an emeritus professor of chemical engineering and
forest resources at the University of Washington and a former dean
of its graduate school. McCarthy taught at the university from 1941
until he retired in 1984, serving as graduate dean from 1957 to
1974. After retiring, he accepted a professorship at Nanjing
Forestry University in China.
</P>
<P>
   His principal research interests were thermodynamics, the
chemistry of cellulose and the development of cleaner techniques in
pulp processing.
</P>
<P>
   McCarthy wrote some 170 scientific papers. His studies took him
to forestry laboratories from Europe to China and earned him an
international reputation.
</P>
</TEXT>
