<P>
   CUBAN-STUDIES (Undated) _ New and surprising discoveries about
Cuban history have only recently become possible for more than a
handful of scholars from the United States as both Washington and
Havana have eased restrictions on research in Cuba. The improved
access and the widely held belief that Cuba is on the cusp of
another historic change has led to a rebirth of Cuban Studies at a
time when public fascination with the country, as evidenced by the
popularity of Cuban music and the national obsession with the Elian
Gonzalez case, is also on the rise. By Laurence Zuckerman. (1800
words)
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photos NYT 1,2 are being sent to NYT photo clients.)
