<P>
   CELIBACY-NYMPHOMANIA (Undated) _ For years, feminist scholars,
sociologists, psychologists and others have studied and charted the
continual shifts in sexual attitudes and practices. Now two
historians are trying to further upend conventional assumptions
about sex, one by studying celibacy, the other by focusing on
nymphomania. By Dinitia Smith. (1400 words)
</P>
<P>
   BELLOW-ROTH (Undated) _ Edwin Rothstein on the writers Saul
Bellow and Philip Roth. (1000 words)
</P>
<P>
   MESSIAEN-OPERA (Undated) _ A critic's notebook on the first U.S.
performance of sections of Olivier Messiaen's opera ``Saint Francis
of Assisi.'' By Paul Griffiths.
