<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGELS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ANGELS FIGHT TO KEEP FOCUS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ With one of their own lying in hospital bed
only a few miles away, the Anaheim Angels tried to go on with
business as usual Friday night against the Texas Rangers.
</P>
<P>
   But the Rangers smashed four home runs _ three off Angels
starter Scott Schoeneweis _ on their way to a 13-11 victory before
35,305 at Edison Field.
</P>
<P>
   Pitcher Kent Mercker is in intensive care at UC Irvine Medical
Center after having a cerebral hemorrhage Thursday night. His
condition is stable but doctors are still trying to determine the
cause of the bleeding in his brain.
</P>
<P>
   Angels manager Mike Scioscia, though, said focusing on the game
would not be a problem for his players.
</P>
<P>
   ``A funny thing happens when you play the game, how instincts
take over,'' Scioscia said. ``You're able to play through tough
things happening off the field. It's not an indication of not
caring or connecting with Kent. Your instincts take over and you
play the game.''
</P>
<P>
   The Angels' problem, however, was that the Rangers batters were
focused at the plate.
</P>
<P>
   They had 14 hits in all, and they weren't cheap as eight went
for extra bases. The four homers were hit by Mike Lamb, Ruben
Mateo, Royce Clayton (grand slam) and Ivan Rodriguez.
</P>
<P>
   Rodriguez also tied a club record with two triples in the game.
David Segui and Mateo each had a double.
</P>
<P>
   Rangers closer John Wetteland pitched the final 1 innings for
his fourth save of the season and No. 300 of his career, becoming
the 12th pitcher to reach the milestone in baseball history. At 33
years, 8 months and 21 days, Wetteland tied Lee Smith as the
youngest to reach 300.
</P>
<P>
   But it didn't come easy.
</P>
<P>
   Wetteland entered the game in the eighth inning with two out.
After giving up an RBI single to Darin Erstad, he retired Adam
Kennedy on a fly to deep center for the third out, the Rangers
maintaining an 11-8 lead.
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers scored twice in the top of the ninth off Angels
reliever Mike Fyhrie, and it turned out they needed the runs
because Wetteland struggled in the bottom of the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   Mo Vaughn led off the inning with a homer and Tim Salmon
doubled. Garret Anderson followed with a two-run homer and
suddenly, a 13-8 game was 13-11 with nobody out.
</P>
<P>
   Troy Glaus grounded out to third for the first out of the ninth,
but Orlando Palmeiro singled to center. Bengie Molina, who had a
career-high four hits including two home runs, this time popped out
for the second out.
</P>
<P>
   Scott Spiezio stuck out to end it.
</P>
<P>
   Salmon's two-run homer in the first inning (No. 9) and an RBI
single by Kennedy in the second staked Schoeneweis to a 3-0 lead.
But the Rangers bounced back quickly.
</P>
<P>
   A two-run homer by Lamb in the third inning made it 3-2. In the
fourth, Rodriguez tripled and scored on a groundout to tie the game
at 3, and two outs later Mateo homered to put the Rangers up, 4-3.
</P>
<P>
   The Angels tied the game at 4 in the fourth on the first of
Molina's two homers, but the Rangers broke it open with five runs
in the sixth, four coming home on Clayton's first career grand
slam.
</P>
<P>
   Molina hit his second homer of the game in the sixth, and
doubled in a run in the eighth, his fourth hit of the game. But the
Angels bullpen, already tired from excessive use, couldn't hold the
Rangers down.
</P>
<P>
   Rodriguez hit the Rangers' fourth homer of the game off Fyhrie
in the seventh inning, and the Rangers added another run in the
eighth and two more in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   For Schoeneweis, Friday's game was his second rough outing in a
row, and his second loss in a row after a 4-0 start. Schoeneweis
gave up a season-worst nine runs and nine hits in six innings.
</P>
<P>
   In his previous start, he gave up six runs (five earned) and six
hits in five innings. His ERA was 3.43 before the past two starts,
but is up to 5.06 now. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
