<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs on
Sunday, May 14, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Gerry Hoppe at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TRADE (Washington) _ Southern California's congressional
representatives stand in the way of a China trade vote that's a top
priority for Hollywood studios, the industries that feed the area's
ports and the White House. By Bill Hillburg. (Will move in the
``a'' national news file and in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CONSENT-DECREES (Los Angeles) _ The Justice Department is
seeking a consent decree for the Los Angeles Police Department to
correct a long pattern of alleged civil rights by officers, the
latest in a series of such agreements that have significantly
changed how a number of Los Angeles agencies - from transportation
to education to sanitation - operate. By Harrison Sheppard. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
