<SLUG> BC-ACTRESS-MOM-ARREST-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DREW BARRYMORE'S MOTHER IS CHARGED WITH GUN POSSESSION 
</HEADLINE>
   By WILLIAM K. RASHBAUM   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Jaid Barrymore, the estranged mother of actress Drew
Barrymore, was charged with gun possession early Saturday after
police officers who arrested her on charges of putting up
promotional posters for a rock band in Soho said they found a
loaded revolver in her purse.
</P>
<P>
   The elder Barrymore, 53, who lives in the East Village, and a
26-year-old man were arrested about 2 a.m. at the corner of Houston
Street and Broadway by police officers from the department's
graffiti unit, said Officer Chris Cottingham, a police spokesman.
</P>
<P>
   Barrymore was charged with third-degree criminal possession of a
weapon, a felony for which she could face a maximum of seven years
in prison if convicted, the authorities said. Both she and the man
she was with, Paul Charnin, 26, of the same address, were charged
with criminal mischief, making graffiti and possession of graffiti
instruments.
</P>
<P>
   The two were putting up posters for the Paul Cote band on a
plywood wall outside a construction site when they were arrested,
Cottingham said.
</P>
<P>
   Barrymore argued with the officers, and said, ``I can't believe
you're arresting me for this,'' Cottingham said.
</P>
<P>
   The officers searched her possessions and found a Ruger .357
Magnum handgun in her purse, Cottingham said.
</P>
<P>
   The pistol had bullets loaded in two of its six chambers, he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Barrymore is often a guest on Howard Stern's radio and
television shows, and has talked publicly about her troubled
relationship with her daughter, Drew, 25, whose successful acting
career has overshadowed her own. Drew Barrymore broke all contact
with her mother about five years ago.
</P>
<P>
   The elder Barrymore, who recently appeared in ``The Dressing
Room,'' a musical now playing at the Soho Playhouse, is reportedly
writing a tell-all book that is said to include stories about what
she says were relationships with actor Jack Nicholson and rock star
Jim Morrison.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
