</P>
<P>
   MOCKINGBIRD-FEVER _ The Monroeville (Ala.) Players are midway
through a 12-show run of a two-act stage version of Harper Lee's
classic novel ``To Kill a Mockingbird.'' Saturday the biggest
``Mockingbird'' fan of all, Mary Badham, who played the tomboy
``Scout'' in the Oscar-winning 1962 film version of the book, will
visit Monroeville, the real-life inspiration for the novel's
setting, for the first time. (Vejnoska, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED
</P>
