<P>
   EDITORS NOTE: WINSTON CUP HAS AN OFF WEEK IN OBSERVANCE OF
MOTHER'S DAY
</P>
<P>
   COXNET INSIDE NASCAR 00512: STEWART'S SOPHOMORE JINX _ If there
is such a thing as a sophomore jinx on the Winston Cup circuit,
Tony Stewart is living it. Heralded during his rookie season as
perhaps the best up-and-coming driver the circuit had seen since
Richard Petty, Stewart hasn't won a thing in 2000. His hard luck
continued at Richmond where bad luck hit once again. (Minter,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
